caption: It was a great experience! They were under staff tonight and our waiter was attentive at making us as happy as possible! They had the cutest decor and I already have told my friend out of town that I am taking them there! Thank you guys so much!

This is such a cool restaurant. I've always driven by it but never got to try it until yesterday. And it was great!! I've been trying to find a good ramen place ever since I went to japan last year. And this one was awesome! The ramen was very tasty. I ordered the shoyu ramen. It was already pretty spicy which I like, but I still added some more spice. But the flavor was great. I also ordered the gyoza, the chicken bao buns, and my friend ordered the chicken karaage. It all was delicious. And soooo glad I found a place that does bao buns. Those are literally my favorite. The atmosphere in the restaurant was so cool. It felt like I was back in Nonbei Yokocho, or drunkards alley. I will definitely be back here. Can't wait to try some more of the food.
Ramen rubbed wings are crispy perfection 🤘🍗🍜!!
We went for my friends birthday and it did not disappoint!! Tristan made sure we had an unforgettable experience!
Such an amazing Japanese ambiance! Loved the place. Prices are moderate. Sakes are fresh and awesome.

Awesome flavor and concept! Place is set up like your in a Japanese/China alley. Food was great! Owner was easy to talk to and easy to talk with. They 16 beers on tap and plenty of sake to try. There is an Old school arcade located up stairs...roughly 20 stand up video games and 5-7 pinball games. Old school classics! Has 2 bars in it one down stairs and one up in the arcade. They also offer take out. It doesn’t look like much from the outside but do yourself a favor and go in.

Chow's has become almost a tradition for our household. Birthdays, family visits, bachelor parties, whatever the case these wonderful people deliver! Even with covid still in its heat, they still are making some of the most amazing food I've had the pleasure of tasting (like their karage chicken rice bowl or their new ramen chicken wings!!!) I've been a chef for about a decade and no matter what I've had here, from simple to complex, or sweet to "booze-tastic" it always sets a new standard for me and my taste buds!
Loved the staff and the food was superb!
Tasty food, fun drinks, and arcade games. What more could you want?
Absolutely loved it 😍 great food awesome service ❤️
Been here a few times love the atmosphere, the food is good, customer service is good and it's an overall welcoming fun experience.
Very tasty food, and friendly staff!

Definitely a cool place to check out if you are in town! The downstairs is a bar/restaurant (they also have some outdoor tables) and the upstairs is an arcade. Call ahead if you want to reserve one of the gaming pods. We ordered a few of their drinks and got mochi for dessert.

Nice place and ambience but the catering services are too poor. We made reservations and when we reached the location, we were informed only appetizers were served. We had to walk back without our meals.

Clean enviroment.friendly staff CANT GET ENOUGH OF THE FOOD!!!! They are currently renting arcade pods $10 an hour now thats a deal! Bartenders are always a good time and they welcome anyone and everyone.Inside is decorated adorbs! Fun atmosphere!!! They are also doing take out! EAT THE BAO BUNS!!! Stay for the FUN BUCKETS!!!😍😍😍😍😍
Very friendly staff. Great atmosphere.  Very well decorated. Food was good and the drinks were a huge hit.
Great service, wonderful cuisine, and delicious libations. Thank you for allowing the Misses to take photos on the pink staircase!  See you again soon.
Great service and great food!
Our last & my favorite stop of the night! Food, service, and ambiance were all top notch.

Fantastic Japanese Street Food with a twist that perfect every time. This place is a Downtown Buffalo gem. They still bring it even with all the COVID-19 rules. Easily the cleanest place I’ve see. They have the policies down. Add the retro arcade games upstairs and their awesome Craft Cocktails, perfect evening out!
This is the coolest place in Buffalo!!! Excellent food, and beautifully crafted drinks. The arcade is super fun, and of course, the insta famous pic stairs for selfies.
Slightly trendy but otherwise okay
Super fun date night place. They're always out of octopus and the pork bao changed. The old recipe was better
The food was great. Just ordered apps and played games. The arcade is super nostalgic and with an adult twist. Because the bar is just right there! I really had an awesome time.
Such a rad place! A must go

Misuta Chow's has an atmosphere that's really like no other in Buffalo. However, it can be a bit hard to enjoy when there's karaoke playing in a smaller area. The drinks fit perfectly with the theme, I'm not sure how the food is because the kitchen was closed when I was there. Despite all the noise, it was a good time.

Amazing food. They just never seem to have enough servers working when we're there. I recommend the gyoza, popcorn, and their chicken ramen when they have it. The popcorn has a bit of a kick to it but I just couldn't stop eating it.

A unique style bar, partial restaurant and partial arcade. A few friends and I spent some time here getting drinks and simply playing the wide assortment of arcade games. As well of course, visiting the infamous pink staircase.

I’m sad to have to write this review because I’ve been here a few times and haven’t had a bad experience until my last visit. Last night myself and 5 others stopped in to celebrate a birthday. Within a few minutes of being there a very intoxicated person at the bar was rude to our group. The same person was friends with the bartender and the staff. The bar tender rudely took a drink order and pushed us away. The same drunk person started to verbally harass our group again and the staff asked my group to leave. After we just purchased drinks for 6 people. I’ve never been mistreated like this at a bar. I’ll never come back and can’t believe management would treat paying customers like this because they were friends with someone who had too much to drink.

I’ve been here 3-4 times and feel comfortable giving 3 stars. The aesthetic and food is the saving grace for this spot. The decor is great and the setup works pretty well. The food is on point and reasonably priced. I like the games they have for the most part but ski-ball is always broken. My biggest complaint here is the service. I have never had a good experience with a bartender or a server. Last night was not at all busy for a snowy Saturday in buffalo, yet the bartenders would rather talk and dance than serve customers. The main bar seemed to have a very inexperienced bartender/bar back team. One upstairs bartender, a large unkempt looking guy, was doing a weird dance trying to get a female patron to put a dollar in his waist band. There were several people waiting to order drinks that were clearly unamused. We keep coming back hoping it improves but are constantly disappointed. I have family coming next week that I was hoping to bring here but I think we will find somewhere else after last nights let down.
One of my favorite places!

This is my new favorite spot in Buffalo!  Awesome food, cool atmosphere, and fun games!

Excellent service, great drinks, food that gets better with every bite, well-run kitchen, and an ambiance and decor that Marshawn "Beast Mode" Lynch would marvel at, Misuta Chow's is the place to go for any occasion.

Oh my goodness. Amazing food! Even when they were "in the weeds" we were sat within 15min, got our drinks, our starter and our entree within 30min. Amazing. They have a nice selection of drinks, the most popular one is the Hello Kitty which has glitter in. Also, there is a parking lot adjacent to the building for $6. Fun little bar with arcade games upstairs and dining downstairs.  Decent happy hour specials too.

Went here for lunch with my family of 3 yesterday. We could not find a parking lot, so we paid for street parking. Atmosphere was spot on and we all enjoyed the ambiance. Floor one was like an alleyway, so tables were close and most could only sit 2-6 people. You could also eat at the counter and watch the cook, which was neat. May be difficult for a wheelchair user to get around, however, or feel cramped if at full capacity. It wasn't too busy being lunch time, but there was only one cook on which meant waiting about 45 minutes for our food which is why I deducted a star. The wait staff was attentive and courteous and was apologetic over the wait. The food was great, flavorful and tasty, although wish the portions were a little bigger. A lot of it was spicy and not listed as such which might be a problem for some people. After lunch, we checked out the games upstairs. My daughter loved the pink stairwell and pony chandelier. There is also stairwell in the front with a gigantic Godzilla mural. Not sure if there is an elevator for those with mobility aids. Floor 2 is another bar and mostly retro cabinet games, think Street Fighter and Punch Out, with a row of 90s pinball machines. One pinball machine (Aerosmith) took our money but seemed to be malfunctioning (we never got a ball to play and there was no one upstairs to complain to). There was also 2 skee ball machines and a fun house mirror. The ceiling has a cool neon light mural. Games were anywhere between 50 cents to $2 to play. There is a 3rd floor of some balcony where smoking was allowed, but we did not go see it. Overall, it was fun atmosphere, family friendly enough in the day time to bring out of town vistors, and the food seemed authentic and definitely was appetizing. Would be interested to see it at night, but not sure I liked it enough to be a repeat visitor.
Stopped in for some lunch on the patio. All the staff were very welcoming and accommodating. Service was quick and my Udon was excellent, highly recommended.

This venue is a little cramped but it is cozy and quaint. There is an upstairs with classic arcade games. The food was good and the atmosphere was fun and relaxed. It wasn't too crazy like lots of bar restaurants can be. I had the Karaage Chicken which is described on the menu as "marinated chicken fried crispy & served with cucumber tofu ranch". As an extremely picky eater who isn't too fond of Asian cuisine (or trying new foods for that matter) I found this dish to be very delicious. For those people experimenting with new cuisine and I would wholeheartedly recommend this dish. We had some fun taking pictures in the back pink stairwell while waiting for a table  and they texted us when our seats were ready. We were seated at the "bar" that is in front of the kitchen area so the chefs were right in front of us. I think it would have been a cooler experience if the bar was a little lower so we could see the cooking better (more like hibachi grill) bit otherwise it was great. I ate half of my meal before I remembered to take a picture so that's why the plate looks half empty. If you try this I hope you enjoy it as much as I did.
